Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @Potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them
onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @Black Beans{1%carton} in a #sieve{}. Pop
half into a small #bowl{} and roughly mash with the back of a #fork{}.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{60%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%grams} and fry until browned,
~{4-5%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Once the beef is browned, drain and discard any excess fat.

Stir in the @Tomato Puree{30%grams} and @Chipotle Paste{20%grams} (add less if
you'd prefer things milder). Fry for ~{1%minute}.

Add the @Water for the Sauce{150%ml}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams} and beans
(whole and mashed). Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat.

Simmer, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the beef simmers, grate the Cheddar.

Once the beef filling is ready, lay your @Super Soft Tortillas with Whole Wheat{4}
onto a lightly oiled baking tray and spoon onto one half of each one. Top with
the grated Cheddar.

Fold the other side over so you have a semi-circle. Press down to keep it
together.

Rub each with a little @oil{}, then bake your quesadillas on the middle shelf
of your oven until golden, ~{8-12%minutes}.

While the quesadillas bake, halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a
#tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out into a bowl.

Season the avocado with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then roughly mash with a fork.
Set your smashed avo aside.

Once the wedges are cooked, crumble over the @Greek Style Salad Cheese{100%grams}.
Return the wedges to the oven to bake until the cheese has slightly browned,
~{5-6%minutes}.

When everything's ready, serve your beef quesadillas with the cheesy wedges,
@soured cream{150%grams} and smashed avo alongside. Enjoy!